Q2. Gather Feedback & Suggest Improvements
How to Gather Feedback (Simple Methods)
Method	How It Works
Quick Survey	3 questions via email or QR code after presentation
Show of Hands	"Who learned something new today?"
Quiz	2–3 simple questions to test understanding
Open Mic	Ask: "What felt unclear?" or "What would you add?"
Sample Feedback Form (3 Questions)
Was the content clear and useful? (👍 / 😐 / 👎)

What part was most helpful? (Open-ended)

What would make this better? (Open-ended)

Common Feedback & Suggested Improvements
Feedback	Improvement
"Too much text on slides."	Use more images, icons, and short bullet points. Show a real fake email example.
"It felt one-sided."	Add interactive elements: a 30-second quiz, "spot the phishing email" game, or Q&A.
"Too long / too short."	Keep it under 10 minutes with a clear takeaway. Offer optional deeper session for interested people.
"Not relevant to my role."	Use department-specific examples (e.g., finance sees fake invoice scams, HR sees fake resumes).
"I forget it afterwards."	Send a 1-page cheat sheet via email and put up reminder posters in common areas.
"No one asked questions."	Offer a digital suggestion box or let people submit questions anonymously.
